                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"will\" data-pf2-dc=\"22\" data-pf2-traits=\"divine,enchantment,incapacitation,mental\" data-pf2-label=\"Dominate DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Will</span></p>\n<hr />\n<p>The vampire can cast <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Dominate]{Dominate}</em> at will as a divine innate spell. Casting it requires staring into the target's eyes, giving the spell the visual trait. The save DC uses the DC of the vampire's level, and a creature that succeeds is temporarily immune to that vampire's Dominate for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>Fully destroying the vampire ends the domination, but merely reducing the vampire to 0 HP is insufficient to break the spell.</p>"
